<br>
.....aww but sleep will erase the troubles of today I am sure - it has always worked before....I must be strong...<br>
<br>
Home a wonderful word now - all my dragons and Peraspera - sweet dear Peraspera...all I can do is sigh in wonder that he should love me so. <br>
<br>
Lost in thought I sense movement ahead ...ahh it is Lady Seriena -  hmm should i speak to her or let her explore the forest, our home, in her own way? Thinking it might be best I silently whisper a spell of protection over her and I venture on home hoping ..as I make sure to leave marks for her tracking ...that she will too follow me home and not be out running with the wolves as she often does. Wolves are nice though....but not much bedfellows..giggling..my mind wanders... oh hush Sonja.... <br>
<br>
Shaking myself I draw my thoughts to tomorrow...thinking sweet Seli should be sleeping - I should step in and tuck her in, tomorrow Lady Whispurr I need to visit and check on her newfound skills with baking...giggling to myself at the thought of the last meal I tried to make - poor Peraspera ate all of it burned bread and all.  <br>
<br>
Mind wandering again I shake my head ...lets see... Lord Balamil - yes a dove sent maybe with some cookies made by Lady Whispurr...a special note to Lady Inkara to comfort her while Lord Balamil is away on his very important journey...a reminder to Lord Linamas to study hard for his next Paladin exam on warfare and celestial healings and also Watchyur to talk to Lildog about sliding down the banister....maybe Lord Deknyr could watch him...humming to myself I lightly hop up the steps and enter the dragon whisper's home...<br>
<br>
Passing thought the halls I notice Lady Thebe standing in front of the fireplace in the family room - shivering ...thinking to myself of my warm bed - Peraspera's arms waiting...I still call out to my sister...silently begging forgiveness from Peraspera for keeping from him...<br>
<br>
&quot;Vendui Lady Thebe - welcome my dear..oh my you are shivering&quot; <br>
<br>
...handing her a glass of deep red wine I wave my hand to the spot on the couch beside me....<br>
<br>
&quot;Please dear sit and talk with me.. I sense you are troubled&quot;<br>
<br>
...sipping my glass..my finger circling the top I watch her...and wait.. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sonjaleah>Sonjaleah</A> at: 3/21/03 9:16:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thebe@voiceofthedragon>Thebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(3/28/03 7:45:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kerncountygas.com/images/girl3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Destiny</span><hr size=1> I trudge wearily through the night towards home.  My only companion is the sound of rustling leaves blowing across the path.  The house can be seen in the distance, but I do not notice.  My mind is somewhere else as I try to make sense of my experience in the forest.  <br>
<br>
I walk up the steps to the door, and open in, yet I am scarcely relieved.  I have so many questions, so many things to think about.  On an ordinary day, being able to be with friends, getting a meal, and having a warm, inviting bed is so comforting; tonight I am possessed by the demons of doubt.  I have not eaten this day but I am not hungry; the long journey has exhausted me, but I could not sleep.<br>
<br>
I stand by the fire.  I stare into it, drawn by the flickering tongues of flame.  Who was that man in the forest?  Why must I fight him?  <br>
<br>
Lady Sonjaleah appears beside me and hands me a glass of wine and asks what is troubling me.<br>
<br>
“I do not know my Lady.  I just met a strange fellow in the forest.  He was surprised I did not know who he was!  I think I am supposed to defeat him in battle some day in the future, and I do not feel I am prepared.”<br>
<br>
“I know so little of these lands, I did not travel far from Qeynos during my training.  I often angered my master… I was often distracted with other things and did not study hard enough.”  <br>
<br>
“I was so unsure of what I wanted to do.  Now that I am older, I am sure I want to be a Rogue.  But I am behind other Rogues of my age, and the work it will take to catch up is daunting.”  <br>
<br>
“I know I must learn many things to prove I am worthy for the journey to the forest, especially blacksmithing to increase the strength of my armor and weapons.  I know my fellow Dragons will always be there when I am in need, but many things I must do myself to be able to stand my ground.”  <br>
<br>
“Alas, I am questioning my skills to do just that…”<br>
