&quot;They would never!&quot; is the white hot thought that blazes through my head. &quot;Never would they all leave me like that!&quot;<br>
<br>
I look to my surroundings. Under the stars, in a forest clearing, upon a slight hill. My campsite. It was all a dream.<br>
<br>
But what a dream, everyone deserted me in it, no one was there when I needed them most. I searched for each after they dissapeared, but to no avail. Alone, forgotten and lost, it had seemed so real.<br>
<br>
I gaze into the crystal that I am certain Sonjaleah left for me and sigh. Perhaps it is their right to leave me, after all, I have been gone a long time. Truely, I meant to be gone such a time not, but life carried me away. Maybe it is not my place to take by all of the dragons anymore.<br>
<br>
I begin to look to the crystal for answers. Friendly faces shine through it. Watching, I see that this is the true feelings of my friends of the dragons. Watchyur, Deknyr, Whispurr, Sicara, Laedil, Sonjaleah, Linamas... they would never forsake me. It was, after all, just a dream. <br>
<br>
Not true, just my mind wandering and leaving me vulnerable to my fears. Still slightly afraid of loss, I sit by my campfire a while to calm my nerves. In my bedroll, I curl up into a tight ball around Amber to challange any further dreams that might haunt me. <br>
<br>
I will not allow them to overcome me. I will hold my head high and know with all my heart that the dragons will not desert me, that they care about me. And when the time comes, and I am of a higher level, I will look after them, my friends, as they have looked after me.<br>
<br>
Though my thoughts are now brave, the immage of loss haunts me as I drift off to sleep. My final thoughts are &quot;Please don't leave me. I couldn't bear that much loss again. I've lost those I care for far too many times already, and though I deserve such friends not, I still care for them.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sonjaleah>Sonjaleah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Scale, Tserrina's best friend</span><br>  Posts: 303<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(3/29/03 7:24:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Family</span><hr size=1> Appearing in a mist - I tiptoe over to Seli and gently gather her in my arms.  Her bed...home is where she needs to be...Amber come help me tuck her in.<br>
<br>
Chanting a magic spell - I open a portal big enough for 2 and Amber and we depart - leaving not a trace.<br>
