<br>
My heart is racing with every step I take...silently, I will my heart to slow down, &quot;Rena remember, no one can see you, you have covered your tracks, and camoed yourself...you are safe.&quot; <br>
<br>
As I approach the spot, I see a marking left near the path, looking ahead I can see many more of these markings....I decide to follow them, hopeing that the marks will lead me to whomever was out here tonight...passing the last of the markings, I find myself at a clearing that holds the whispers domain...A smile forms upon my lips, finally a place to call home...family and friends...<br>
<br>
I remove the spell I cast upon myself, knowing now, that it was Lady Sonjaleah...leader of the dragons...of whisper...she was the one in the forest tonight...the one who left the markings for me to follow...<br>
<br>
As I enter, I see the fire blazing in the hearth...slowly walking over to the fire, I place my pack beside me and pull out a bottle of white wine...pouring myself a glass, I sit down and gaze into the fire...<br>
<br>
The smile that was once upon my lips fades, and I am left with only the memories and doubts that I fear will haunt me for the rest of my days...I think of my new found family and friends...I hope and pray that Tunare will cast her blessings on each and everyone of them...<br>
<br>
Pulling my gaze away from the fire, I look into the swirling golden liquid that is in the glass cradled in my hands, and tears begin to burn behind my eyes as I think of all my memories, and of my fellow dragons.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=top69dawg@voiceofthedragon>top69dawg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(3/30/03 9:18:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> what i am and what i can never be</span><hr size=1> as a young ranger I remember following my friend as he taught me the way down from my home in the tree's. but alas those days are gone<br>
the days when I would come home to my native land's of kelethin with wonderful prizes for my fellow rangers who were just starting journey's into these land's, mere trinkets to me, as I grin and chuckle to myself.<br>
since those days i have met people through my travels, some call me friend some do not. <br>
as well I met up with some dragons, who have seen and done many wonderouse things worthy of song and story indeed occasionally I par take in their raids that I can make it to. while in the moment I enjoy the comradery but then I remember I am to never truly be apart of any thing. I am merely to forage my food, develop my fighting skills by tracking down my prey and laying waste to it and make my wares so I might afford better weapons as needed.<br>
for the world can be a very dangerous and unkind place for a ranger.<br>
I take solace in the knowledge that any traveler I might pass need not worry of death, for I will stop and whisper my kind word of healing and grant them skin like stone for a time. so they might further in there endeavors.<br>
then I slip back into the darkness and continue on my path of solitude to what end I know not.<br>
some day to a home? I do not dare dream.<br>
for being a child to none and a whipping boy to all, except a kind few who took pity.<br>
all I own is the pain and darkness in my heart that i hide away when any draw near that I do not call foe. for the pain would be more then they could bear. as for the darkness I fear that if I ever fully released it what I am now would disappear and I would no longer be a champion of those who have nothing.<br>
so I am truly no where and every where all at once and I fear 1 day the darkness will consume me as I fall into the light. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerielldachanel>Aeriell Dachanel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Green Snake</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/30/03 7:34:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: seriena's journey cont.</span><hr size=1> Blinking away the tears, I finish my glass of wine and put the bottle and the glass back in my pack....making a mental note to remember to wash the glass before I use it again.....I quickly pick my pack up off the floor, and put it over my shoulder...my right hand clasps the twin pendants that hang from necklaces....as I head out once again into the night forest.....<br>
<br>
These pendants, are the exact same....both are shaped like stars, but in the middle of each one a unicorn lays asleep in the moonlight.....Tunare knows that if it were not for the magical sleeping aid properties of the pendants, I would have gone many nights without sleep.....<br>
<br>
Once out of the clearing of the whisper's domain, I am hit yet again with the memories of that dreadful night...the night I lost both of my parents because of my own failures...this time, as I walk the forest, instead of blinking the tears away, I let them fall fast and silent leaving the stained trail along my cheeks and dampening my dress....<br>
<br>
It was a calm and quiet night in the forest....one much like tonight...my father and mother had been out in the forest trying to gather different supplies that we needed when they were attacked by a group of raiders....my father and mother both fought them off, and successfully finished the fight...but alas neither were lucky enough to not get cut by the raiders deeply poisonous blades.....<br>
<br>
I remember I was sitting by the fire when my father came into the house carrying my mother...the both of them looked so pale and sickly...I followed him back into their bedroom where he placed my mother on the bed and as quickly as he could, he started casting magic on her...he said it was to help heal her wounds and drive the poison from her body....he worked for hours it seemed paying no attention to his own wounds....exhausting himself as he tried to save her...but alas the poison had already gone to far...I watched as my mother took her last breath and fell limp in my fathers arms....<br>
<br>
I remember my father then turned to me and said &quot;Rena come here, I need you to help me...&quot; he said that he was injured also, and that I would have to use the magic that he and my mother taught me to help him....and so I did....I worked all night, using herbs and what little magic I knew to try to heal him...I exhausted myself in trying....but to no avail....for as dawns light stretched across the sky I watched as he too took his last breath from this world....and it was all because I his own daughter...his only daughter could not save him from the poison in his veins....and so, all alone I took them both behind the house and buried them...the only thing I kept, were the pendants they both wore, and now I wear as the only reminder I have of them.....<br>
<br>
Lifting my head to look around, I realize that I have wandered deep into the forest...as I look to my left, I see a person laying on the ground....wiping the tears from my eyes, and forgetting my demons for this moment, I head over to the person hopeing that maybe I can help him....he should not be alone in the night forest.....as I approach, I see that it is Lord Peraspera....I stop next to him and lean down....gently I place a hand on his arm so not to startle him....I whisper, &quot;my lord it is Lady Seriena&quot;....to my horror my voice is thick with tears...he looks up, and in his eyes I can tell that he too has demons that only he can fight....and in that moment I realize, that I can indeed help him....as he looks at me, I sit down beside him and tell him that I know all to well what he is going through...I still have my own demons that I deal with every night while I am awake....and I know that the demon or demons you deal with, are something that only you alone can fight.....however, I want you to know that if you ever need a friend, I will be here for you....<br>
<br>
Never taking my eyes off his, I tell him that I want him to have something....and I reach up behind my neck, and remove one of the two necklaces I wear....removing the pendant, I place it in his hand and tell him &quot; always keep the pendant on you for eventhough you may not know the reason behind the pendant, or understand its meaning now, you will one day...let the winds and the unicorn guide you and you will find your sanctuary.&quot; &quot;My lord, the pendant has a twin, and I am the one who wears it...I hope that the pendant you now hold will help you as much as its twin has helped me.....and may you always have peaceful dreams tonight, and for all the nights to come....&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerielldachanel>Aeriell Dachanel</A> at: 4/30/03 7:35:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bvoiceofthedragon.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sonjaleah>Sonjaleah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Scale, Tserrina's best friend</span><br>  Posts: 349<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/30/03 9:20:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/fvoiceofthedragonfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Home</span><hr size=1> Whispering into my looking crystal....<br>
